Crocodilurus is a lizard genus that belongs to the family Teiidae. It is  monotypic, with only a single described species Crocodilurus amazonicus, the crocodile tegu. It is locally known as the Jacarerana. This semiaquatic lizard has a flattened, paddle-like tail and is found in the Amazon Basin and Guiana Shield in South America. It feeds on arthropods, amphibians, reptiles and fish. It is not closely related to Crocodilians.